title: Excitation functions and angular distributions of alpha particles from proton bombardment of 26Mg.

x4freetext: Excitation functions and angular distributions of alpha
particles from proton bombardment of 26Mg.
Two 300 omega*cm silicon surface barrier
counters were arranged at a radial distance of 6.35 cm
from the target with one counter fixed and the other
rotatable from outside.
The 26Mg targets were made from electromagnetically
enriched MgO (magnesium was collected on a thin
self-supporting carbon foil). Targets made in this
fashion were very thin and measurements made on natural
magnesium targets using proton elastic scattering
indicated that thicknesses of less than 1 mu-g/cm2 were
obtained. The targets were mounted in a small target
chamber of 17.7 cm inside diameter.
Energy error (including calibration accuracy,
beam stability and target thickness)
Statistical errors in the total counts of
each alpha particle group over most of the range lie
between 1% and 5% and the background subtracted varies
between 1% and 8% of the total counts with a large
relative error possible in this amount.
